<HEADLINE>
<P>
WELCOME TO HOCKEY WORLD, WHERE KINGS RULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As your team starts a second-round playoff game, it is appropriate for a coach 
to show support for his team by wearing: 
</P>
<P>
A -- The team colors. 
</P>
<P>
B -- Anything but the opposing team's colors. 
</P>
<P>
C -- Nothing. 
</P>
<P>
D -- The opposing team's colors. 
</P>
<P>
Well, if you're Robbie Ftorek of the L.A. Kings, the answer is D. But of 
course, don't we all remember Tommy Lasorda wearing a Mets' hat? 
</P>
<P>
JONATHAN E. MILLER 
</P>
<P>
Reseda 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
