<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: POLICE INTERVENE IN BID TO END GANG FEUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In what authorities called an effort to end a continuing war between two gangs, 
a task force of 125 Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies raided and searched 
11 alleged gang hangouts Friday in Norwalk and Santa Fe Springs. 
</P>
<P>
Nine guns were seized during the searches of homes where members of the two 
gangs are known to live or hang out, Deputy Hal Grant said. Two suspected gang 
members were arrested for resisting arrest and a third for possession of a 
controlled substance, he said. 
</P>
<P>
On April 15, members of the gangs had a gun battle at Los Nietos Park in Santa 
Fe Springs in which one youth was wounded in the stomach, Grant said. "In order 
to prevent further bloodshed and minimize their activities," he said, deputies 
acquired search warrants for the homes to seize weapons. 
</P>
<P>
The raids were conducted by the Operation Safe Streets' anti-gang teams at 1 
p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
