<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gibraltar Won't Seek to Remove Regulators: Gibraltar Financial Corp. of Beverly 
Hills, parent of two still-solvent savings and loans that federal regulators 
seized last month, said it will not seek to remove the regulators from running 
the thrifts. The company said the decision stemmed from its belief that, if it 
took such an action, the Federal Home Loan Bank Board would withhold its 
cooperation and assistance and a liquidity crisis would result. Regulators 
seized the thrifts March 31, saying they were being operated in an unsound 
manner and had dissipated their assets. 
</P>
