Following are capsule reviews of a selection of the screenings today and Sunday 
at the American Film Institute Los Angeles International Film Festival at the 
Cineplex Odeon Cenutry Plaza Cinemas. 
</P>
<P>
SUNDAY 
</P>
<P>
'Woman Demon Human' 
</P>
<P>
China, 1988, 106 minutes 
</P>
<P>
Noon 
</P>
<P>
 Huang Shuquin, one of China's few women film makers, finds complex meanings 
and considerable ambiguity in her story of an actress coming to terms with her 
life and career in this exquisitely nuanced and strikingly original film. Her 
heroine has from her youth defied convention in insisting on playing male roles 
in the Chinese opera which require mastery of martial arts and gymnastics. 
There's an interplay between Qiu's fascination with a demon in a popular opera 
and in her own independent nature that gives the film a strong feminist spirit. 
RECOMMENDED KEVIN THOMAS 
