<P>
Following are capsule reviews of a selection of the screenings today and Sunday 
at the American Film Institute Los Angeles International Film Festival at the 
Cineplex Odeon Cenutry Plaza Cinemas. 
</P>
<P>
SUNDAY 
</P>
<P>
'I'm the One You're Looking For' 
</P>
<P>
Spain, 1988, 90 minutes 
</P>
<P>
4:45 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
A beautiful model falls in love with her biker rapist and pursues him 
obsessively through the dangerous, lower-class dives of Barcelona, taking as 
her accomplices an embittered lady taxi driver and a gentle voyeur-transvestite 
artiste. That's the explosive subject of this Gabriel Garcia Marquez-scripted 
fable. But it's the weakest of the "Dangerous Love" series. Director Jaime 
Chavarri has a rudimentary, flat style; he can't work up the whiff of danger or 
eroticism, so the script's deliberate provocations, embedded in an emotionless 
drift, seem simply shocking or shallow. MICHAEL WILMINGTON 
</P>
