<P>
MT. SAC RELAYS; 
</P>
<P>
MCGRANN, STERLING TO RUN DISTANCE EVENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Distance runners Beth McGrann and Brigid Sterling lead UC Irvine's entries in 
the university and open divisions of the Mt. San Antonio College Relays. 
Competition in the two divisions begins this afternoon and continues on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
McGrann set a school record of 33 minutes 45 seconds and qualified for the 
National Collegiate Athletic Assn. meet in the 10,000 meters last year at Mt. 
SAC. 
</P>
<P>
McGrann is entered in the 10,000, scheduled for tonight at 9:30, and the 5,000 
Sunday at 9:40 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Sterling, the Big West Conference cross-country champion last fall, will run 
the 3,000 at 8:05 tonight and the invitational 1,500 on Sunday at 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Geerlings, a freshman from Newport Harbor who was Orange County's top high 
school miler last season with a best of 4:10.43, will compete in the distance 
medley relay tonight at 7:50 and the 1,500 Sunday at 11:30 a.m. 
</P>
